From: Anjali Singhai Jain <anjali.singhai@intel.com>
Date: Thu, 28 Nov 2013 06:39:46 +0000
Subject: [PATCH v3 140/474] i40e: check asq alive before notify
Patch-mainline: v3.14-rc1
Git-commit: 37f0be6d297a5e32b7b2873a0d6d687e685948bc
References: bsc#909484 FATE#317397

Driver needs to make sure the send queue is alive before
trying to use it.

Chagne-Id: I9bd1f6159c45c98e63f562e3a8dfb57edfe50e13
Signed-off-by: Anjali Singhai Jain <anjali.singhai@intel.com>
Signed-off-by: Jesse Brandeburg <jesse.brandeburg@intel.com>
Tested-by: Kavindya Deegala <kavindya.s.deegala@intel.com>
Signed-off-by: Jeff Kirsher <jeffrey.t.kirsher@intel.com>
Acked-by: David Chang <dchang@suse.com>
---
 drivers/net/ethernet/intel/i40e/i40e_main.c |    3 ++-
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/intel/i40e/i40e_main.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/intel/i40e/i40e_main.c
@@ -4770,7 +4770,8 @@ static int i40e_prep_for_reset(struct i4
 
 	dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev, "Tearing down internal switch for reset\n");
 
-	i40e_vc_notify_reset(pf);
+	if (i40e_check_asq_alive(hw))
+		i40e_vc_notify_reset(pf);
 
 	/* quiesce the VSIs and their queues that are not already DOWN */
 	i40e_pf_quiesce_all_vsi(pf);
